==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[pro#Latin|pro]]'', before + ''[[testis#Latin|testis]]'', [[witness]]

===Pronunciation===
*(''verb''): prətĕst', /prəˈtɛst/, /<tt>pr@"tEst</tt>/
*(''noun''):
**(''[[RP]]''): /ˈprəʊtɛst/, /<tt>"pr@UtEst</tt>/
**(''US''): prō'tĕst, /ˈproʊtɛst/, /<tt>"proUtEst</tt>/
[[Category:English heteronyms]]

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|protest||}}
# to make a strong [[objection]]
#:''How dare you, I '''protest'''!''
#:''The public took to the streets to protest over the planned change to the law.''

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|protest||}}
# to [[affirm]] something
#:''I '''protest''' my innocence.''
#(''mostly US'') to [[object]] to something
#:''They '''protested''' the demolition of the school.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
{{wikipedia}}

# A [[formal]] [[objection]], especially one by a [[group]]
# A [[collective]] [[gesture]] of [[disapproval]], sometimes [[violent]]

